list.item:
Sec. 3. If at any time during the absence from the seat of government, an occasion shall arise requiring a declaration of martial law, or suspension of the writ of habeas corpus, the powers in and concerning such matters herein granted to the President may be exercised by one of the cabinet ministers, who shall act in order of priority below named, each succeeding in case of disability or failure of those previously named to act, viz:
The minister of foreign affairs;
The minister of interior;
The minister of finance;
The attorney-general.

frus:attachment.p:
Section 5. The electors in the said
                                districts shall be entitled to elect Representatives as follows: 

In the First district, two;

In the Second district, two;

In the Third district, three;

In the Fourth district, three;

In the Fifth district, three;

In the Sixth district, two.
